Dr Tomasz Forfa is an Australian Medical Doctor and Entrepreneur whose purpose is to change the face of Australian Medicine for the better.  

As an entrepreneur, Tomasz has developed several companies, one of these companies known as PassGAMSAT has helped over 45,000 aspiring future Doctors. 
His company has flourished in the tough student marketplace with a niche offering that has helped people prepare for the Australian and UK medical school admissions test known as the GAMSAT.

Tomasz passion didn't stop there, his second company, The Doctors' Collective follows on his from own journey throughout Medical School into the Medical World. The Doctors' Collective is a movement dedicated to helping Australian Doctors' live their best lives. Tomasz envisions a future where Doctors' can live the 'work-life balance', avoid burnout and use the skills they already have to create more time and a better quality of life. 

Tomasz involvement in the community has led him to run the Barefoot Bali campaign which provides disadvantaged Balinese School Children with proper clothing and shoes. Tomasz also has spoken and attended the Creative Careers in Medicine Symposium in May this year.

Tomasz's ability to identify gaps in the marketplace and fill them with his brilliant innovative ideas has transformed the lives of thousands. His skills in marketing, sales, finance and medicine combined with his natural ability of entrepreneurialism is creating a new wave of thinking about medicine in the 21st century.

jobs.description:
Smarter SMSF (formerly The SMSF Academy) was founded by Aaron Dunn and Ian Glenister with a view to "bridging the gap" in training, education and tools to assist professionals growing their business through the use of self managed super funds.

The SMSF Academy developed the SMSF online course, SMSF101, which provides professionals with the most innovative e-learning product ever seen in the self managed super fund sector.

The SMSF Academy delivers through a membership based program:

✮ Regular webinar training including quarterly updates & special topics, '
✮ Technical resource library to keep-up-date with the latest issues
✮ SMSF which enables you to build SMSF documents including trust deeds, pensions and more
✮ Ready-to-use content for members to utilise in their business

The membership model is designed specifically to help practitioners understand their SMSF business model and to assist in the development, delivery and support to help attract, retain and grow their SMSF revenues.

SMSF360 delivers services to trustees around the entire life cycle of their self managed super fund.  

SMSF360 focuses on the delivery of services to High Net Wealth SMSFs, providing fund administration directly to trustees, but also through adviser relationships.  

Our business focus is on providing client's with high-level strategic advice that will provide significant tax benefits now and for future generations using a SMSF.  

We work closely with our referral partner financial advisory groups to build strategies and provide technical support to enhance their client's SMSF Wealth.

SMSF101 Pty Ltd is a joint initiative of The SMSF Academy and Money101 that delivers online SMSF education.  Built by industry experts, SMSF101 delivers highly interactive online education and professional development content that can provide a pathway to SMSF specialisation.

The SMSF101 adviser course is the first truly online SMSF solution in the marketplace today.

The SPAA State Chapters provide a range of networking and educational opportunities for SPAA members and other SMSF professionals.

The Victorian Chapter regularly holds sessions in Melbourne  in both the morning and evenings for its members and other interested attendees at the Amora Hotel in Richmond.  In addition, sub-chapters also operate in Bendigo and Albury where meetings are held on a quarterly basis.  

The regular SPAA Victorian Chapter events provide attendees with high-quality presenters sharing knowledge across financial planning, accounting, auditing, legal, actuarial and other important aspects of SMSFs.  All sessions encourage active participation to held practitioners within their day-to-day work with SMSFs.

The Victorian Chapter encourages new members, and looks to foster engagement between SPAA and its members.

general.description:
Michelle was appointed Bank of Melbourne’s Chief Executive in 2017. She leads a team of passionate Victorians who deliver exceptional service to more than half a million customers through an extensive branch network across metropolitan Melbourne and regional Victoria.

Together with her dynamic executive team and advisory board chaired by Elizabeth Proust, Michelle oversees a unique banking culture that’s integrated into local communities and has strong links to Victoria’s economic prosperity. With an offering that spans retail banking, business banking (including SME and property finance), and private banking, Bank of Melbourne is Victoria’s uniquely local banking alternative. 

Bank of Melbourne has a proud heritage of supporting Victorians that stretches back to 1957. Since it was re-launched in 2011, it has backed the organisations and institutions that make Victoria one of the world’s most liveable places. The bank established its own charitable foundation in 2013, which has supported more than 100 local charities with $2.5 million in grants, making a difference to over 500,000 Victorians who need a helping hand.
